)ATTR DEFAULT(%+_)
    % TYPE(TEXT) INTENS(HIGH) COLOR(WHITE) SKIP(ON)
    Ö TYPE(TEXT) INTENS(HIGH) COLOR(YELLOW)
    + TYPE(TEXT) INTENS(LOW)  COLOR(TURQ) SKIP(ON)
    _ TYPE(INPUT) INTENS(HIGH) CAPS(ON) JUST(LEFT) COLOR(RED)
    ^ TYPE(INPUT) INTENS(HIGH) CAPS(ON) JUST(LEFT) COLOR(RED) PAD(_)
    | TYPE(INPUT) INTENS(HIGH) CAPS(OFF)
)BODY EXPAND(\\)
%TUTORIAL  +-\-\-ÖAlias Update+-\-\-
%OPTION  ===>_ZCMD
+
+ MEMLIST prompt     %===>    + (Yes/No)  LKED Date for load %===>    +
+ Alias check        %===>    + (Yes/No)  Auto member update %===)    +
+ Remove deleted mem %===>    + (Yes/No)  Remove old members %===>    +
% Alias update       %===>+???  (Yes/No)  Save in profile    %===>    +

%Alias update:+
   Normally, when you edit a member and save it, none of it's alias are
   changed to point to the new member.  By setting this option to YES
   then an EDIT is done as a line command on a memlist, PDS will read
   the whole directory for alias and will update the TTR pointer to
   point to the new member.

)END
